<subSubSection id="C33C6549CA40FFAFCD9D3BEFF612F7E6" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9936C2CA40FFAFCD9D3BEFF612F7E6" blockId="16.[2034,2626,1631,2052]" lastBlockId="16.[1423,2625,2058,2642]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">
<emphasis id="B952EAD0CA40FFAFCD9D3BEFF773F798" box="[2040,2293,2023,2052]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 
<quantity id="4CDE9B27CA40FFAFC3CB3BEFF5BCF798" box="[2478,2618,2023,2052]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" unit="cm" value="37.5" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="35.0">35-40 cm</quantity>
, tail 
<quantity id="4CDE9B27CA40FFAFCFAC3402F9D6F7B7" box="[1481,1616,2058,2091]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" unit="cm" value="16.5" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="16.0">16-17 cm</quantity>
; weight about 
<quantity id="4CDE9B27CA40FFAFCD403402F8E4F7B7" box="[1829,1890,2058,2091]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" unit="kg" value="2.0">2 kg</quantity>
. The Javan Ferret-badger has a small, slender body, and a long snout. The pelage is dark brown, with paler undersides. The head is black with a facial mask consisting of white or yellow patches. The skull is small.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6549CA40FFAFCFF53488F8C1F73D" box="[1424,1863,2176,2209]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B9936C2CA40FFAFCFF53488F8C1F73D" blockId="16.[1423,2625,2058,2642]" box="[1424,1863,2176,2209]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">
<emphasis id="B952EAD0CA40FFAFCFF53488FA79F73D" box="[1424,1535,2176,2209]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">Habitat.</emphasis>
Forests and grasslands.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6549CA40FFAFCFF534AFF864F754" box="[1424,2018,2215,2248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph id="8B9936C2CA40FFAFCFF534AFF864F754" blockId="16.[1423,2625,2058,2642]" box="[1424,2018,2215,2248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">
<emphasis id="B952EAD0CA40FFAFCFF534AFF913F754" box="[1424,1685,2215,2248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
Said to be omnivorous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6549CA40FFAFCFEA34DBF877F76C" box="[1423,2033,2259,2288]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" type="activity">
<paragraph id="8B9936C2CA40FFAFCFEA34DBF877F76C" blockId="16.[1423,2625,2058,2642]" box="[1423,2033,2259,2288]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">
<emphasis id="B952EAD0CA40FFAFCFEA34DBF9FFF76C" box="[1423,1657,2259,2288]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Reported to be nocturnal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6549CA40FFAFCFF534F2F90CF6A3" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B9936C2CA40FFAFCFF534F2F90CF6A3" blockId="16.[1423,2625,2058,2642]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">
<emphasis id="B952EAD0CA40FFAFCFF534F2F7DFF68B" box="[1424,2137,2298,2327]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
Terrestrial, but also said to be an agile tree climber.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6549CA40FFAFCFF43541F7F3F6FA" box="[1425,2165,2377,2406]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" type="breeding">
<paragraph id="8B9936C2CA40FFAFCFF43541F7F3F6FA" blockId="16.[1423,2625,2058,2642]" box="[1425,2165,2377,2406]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">
<emphasis id="B952EAD0CA40FFAFCFF43541F991F6FA" box="[1425,1559,2377,2406]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">Breeding.</emphasis>
Littersize is said to vary from one to three.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6549CA40FFAFCFF43564F6FBF59F" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8B9936C2CA40FFAFCFF43564F6FBF59F" blockId="16.[1423,2625,2058,2642]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">
<emphasis id="B952EAD0CA40FFAFCFF43564F976F611" box="[1425,1776,2412,2445]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient in The 
<collectionCode id="ED37AE07CA40FFAFC2823564F6B1F611" box="[2279,2359,2412,2445]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">IUCN</collectionCode>
Red List. Recorded recently in 
<collectingRegion id="49E2F820CA40FFAFCC57359FF95AF628" box="[1586,1756,2455,2484]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Tengah" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">Central Java</collectingRegion>
(perhaps Dieng 
<collectingRegion id="49E2F820CA40FFAFCDB5359FF7BAF628" box="[2000,2108,2455,2484]" country="Nigeria" name="Plateau" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">Plateau</collectingRegion>
), Gunung Halimun Nature Reserve, and Gunung Gede. Very little is known about this species and field studies are needed to learn more aboutits natural history, ecology, and conservation status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33C6549CA40FFAFCFF73619F7A2F5CE" pageId="16" pageNumber="635" type="bibRefCitation_list">
<paragraph id="8B9936C2CA40FFAFCFF73619F7A2F5CE" blockId="16.[1423,2625,2058,2642]" pageId="16" pageNumber="635">
